sections.title: Team Management Profile
sections.vectorChunk: TMP Profile for Sub One at BHP. Major role: Upholder Maintainer (score 8, 19%). Related roles: Controller Inspector (score 7, 15%) and Thruster Organiser (score 5, 14%). Right-side wheel dominant indicating preference for structure, control, and maintaining standards.

sections.title: Introduction

content.mainText: Your personal Team Management Profile provides you with information about your work preferences. It is a starting point for consideration and discussion of how you approach your work and your interactions with others in the workplace.

nineActivities.introduction: All work teams need to consider nine key activities essential for high-performance:

activities.name: Developing
activities.description: Assessing and testing the applicability of new approaches

activities.name: Organising
activities.description: Establishing and implementing ways of making things work

activities.name: Inspecting
activities.description: Controlling and auditing the working of systems

activities.name: Maintaining
activities.description: Upholding and safeguarding standards and processes

activities.name: Linking
activities.description: Coordinating and integrating the work of others

content.profileExplanation: Your own work preferences have been derived from your responses to the Team Management Profile Questionnaire. While you may work in any of the areas of the Wheel, your highest preference area, or Major Role, has been identified together with two Related Roles which indicate your next highest preference areas.

data.summary: Simplified wheel showing your three key roles highlighted

sections.vectorChunk: Introduction for Sub One at BHP. Key preference areas: Organising, Controlling, Advising. Major role: Upholder Maintainer.
